# Blog Files Directory

This folder contains all blog post markdown files.

## How to add a new blog post:

1. Create a new .md file in this folder (e.g., `my-blog-post.md`)
2. Write your blog content in markdown format
3. Add the blog metadata to `src/data/blogs.ts`
4. Make sure the `file_name` in the metadata matches your .md file name

## Markdown file example:

```markdown
# My Blog Post Title

Published: January 15, 2025

## Introduction

Your introduction here...

## Main Content

Your main content with **bold text**, *italic text*, and more.

### Code Examples

```python
def hello_world():
    print("Hello, World!")
```

## Conclusion

Your conclusion here...
```

## Note:
- Files in this directory will be read and rendered on the blog page
- Supports standard markdown syntax
- Images can be referenced from `/public/images/blog/` folder
